# scripts/rnbd/receipts/

This directory holds the SIC-issued PDF receipts that prove our RNBD
(Registro Nacional de Bases de Datos) registration.

## Workflow

1. After submitting the RNBD registration via the SIC portal, save the
   issued PDF here with a date-prefixed filename:
   ```
   scripts/rnbd/receipts/2026-06-26-rnbd-receipt.pdf
   ```
2. Upload to the immutable S3 bucket:
   ```
   bash scripts/rnbd/upload-receipt.sh scripts/rnbd/receipts/2026-06-26-rnbd-receipt.pdf
   ```
3. The script will Object-Lock the file (COMPLIANCE mode, 7y retention).
4. After successful upload, the local PDF copy can be deleted — the
   authoritative artifact is the S3 object.

## What's in the receipts

- **Initial RNBD registration** (Ley 1581/2012 Art. 25 + Decreto 1377/2013
  Art. 42) — the proof we are registered as a database operator.
- **Annual RNBD update** (Decreto 1377/2013 Art. 43, due 2 Jan – 31 Mar
  each year) — proves we kept the registration current.
- **Re-certificaciones** — if Opita Code changes its razón social or
  address, we re-certify; the new receipt is appended here.

## Local copies — operator convenience only

The local PDFs in this directory are convenience copies for the DPO.
They are NOT the authoritative artifact. If this directory is wiped,
nothing is lost: the S3 Object Lock guarantees immutability.